<span id="freeTextContainer530099270158925603">This is my second Hellman play, and I&apos;m definitely interested in more of her work after being mesmerized by this and The Little Foxes. I connected with Martha&apos;s character right from the beginning -- her sarcasm, her cynicism, and by the end, her desperation were all wholly real to me. <br/><br/>I&apos;m also glad to see I&apos;m not the only one who envisioned a link between Mary Tilford and Abigail Williams from The Crucible. What a spiteful little brat. </span>
